ent vital values (76 → 102 bpm), current lab values (lactate 3.2), patient context (post-op day 2 from colon resection), and a multi-sentence clinical narrative.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     67[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     68[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThis is a substantial PHI surface for downstream paging or messaging-platform consumers. Pager / Vocera / TigerConnect / Spok / Mobile Heartbeat notifications are visible on lock screens, in shared logs, in mobile push notifications that appear in the device's notification shade, and in SMS or pager messages that are visible to anyone in the vicinity of the device. The sample narrative ("Risk score has increased substantially over the last 4 hours, driven primarily by rising heart rate (76 to 102 bpm), rising respiratory rate (16 to 22), a lactate of 3.2, and temperature trend rising 1.4°C above baseline. Pattern is consistent with early sepsis. Patient is post-op day 2 from colon resection. Blood cultures have been ordered, suggesting bedside team has noted concern. Suggest sepsis bundle evaluation: full set of vitals, repeat lactate, source review, and consideration of empiric antibiotic timing per local sepsis protocol. This is decision support; clinical judgment governs.") is explicit clinical content that would be disclosive on a lock screen.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     69[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     70[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mRecipe 3.1's expert review settled the chapter discipline: notifications carry the alert ID only, and the consuming application fetches the full record by ID through an authenticated path so the notification channel never carries PHI. Recipes 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6 reaffirmed and extended the discipline. Recipe 3.7's pseudocode does not state the discipline in Step 7. A reader who treats the pseudocode as the implementation specification will produce a system where the full alert payload (including current vital values and the clinical narrative) reaches pager / Vocera / TigerConnect channels, lock screens, and downstream paging-system logs.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     71[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     72[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThis is the now-recurring chapter-3 PHI-minimization-inside-the-BAA pattern with a recipe-3.7-distinctive amplification: the explanation narrative is itself the PHI-carrying field. For Recipes 3.4 and 3.5 the high-stigma test class (drug-of-abuse panel, HIV viral load) was the disclosure concern; for Recipe 3.7 the disclosure includes the entire deterioration phenotype (early sepsis), the post-operative status, current vital values, current lab values, and a clinical-recommendation-shaped narrative that is itself sensitive in ways beyond per-patient PHI. A patient whose lock screen shows "Risk score has increased substantially over the last 4 hours, driven primarily by rising heart rate ... pattern is consistent with early sepsis ... post-op day 2 from colon resection" has had their entire current clinical status disclosed.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     73[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Update Step 7 pseudocode to make the payload-minimization discipline explicit. The EventBridge / SNS / pager-integration message carries only [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140malert_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtier[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, and minimal location attribute (e.g., [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140munit_code[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m); the consuming application (the pager integration Lambda, the Vocera integration Lambda, the TigerConnect integration Lambda) fetches the full alert (including the explanation narrative) by [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140malert_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m through an authenticated path with appropriate IAM scope on the alert state DynamoDB table and the alert audit index. PHI does not transit through pager or messaging platforms or any logs they generate. Add a one-line note: "For pager / Vocera / TigerConnect / SMS channels, the notification subject and body carry only the alert ID, the tier, the unit code, and a generic call-to-action ('High-tier deterioration alert; see chart for details'); the clinician opens the chart through their authenticated EHR session to see the full explanation, the structured drivers, and the narrative. The narrative explanation is sensitive content (current vital values, current lab values, deterioration phenotype, surgical context) and must not transit lock-screen-visible channels." Update the sample alert payload in Expected Results to show the minimal pager-channel payload separately from the full alert record stored in the alert state DynamoDB table and the OpenSearch alert audit index. Add to Prerequisites IAM row a per-consumer scope: pager-integration Lambda role can read alert state and alert audit index by alert_id only; cannot read other alerts in the same patient's history without explicit case-context elevation; bedside nurse roles can read full alert payload only on their assigned patients.[K
