[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    116[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mAlso missing: minimum-necessary prompt construction discipline (the recipe's Step 6 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mbuild_explanation_prompt[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m carries [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mrisk_tier[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcalibrated_probability[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mscore_change[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtop_drivers[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprotective_factors[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpatient_context_summary[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140munit_type[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m; the patient_context_summary is unspecified but a naive implementation would carry the entire patient state including demographics, problem list, medication list, and surgical history); output filtering for clinical-recommendation hallucinations (an LLM that says "give the patient antibiotics now" instead of "consider sepsis bundle evaluation per local protocol" produces evidentiary problems for the FDA CDS exemption posture); and a full prompt-and-response audit trail tied to the alert ID. Same finding shape as Recipes 3.3 V2, 3.4 S4, 3.5 S5, 3.6 S7.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    117[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the Bedrock paragraph: "Bedrock with Amazon foundation models (Titan, Nova) is HIPAA-eligible under the BAA; third-party models on Bedrock (Anthropic Claude, Meta Llama, others) have differing BAA postures, and the model's terms of service must be reviewed before PHI-bearing prompts are sent. Construct prompts with minimum-necessary context (the top SHAP-driven feature names and values; the calibrated probability; the unit type and a coarse patient context like 'post-op day 2'; not the full chart). Filter outputs for clinical-recommendation language: the LLM should produce evaluation-suggestion language ('suggest sepsis bundle evaluation per local protocol') rather than treatment-decision language ('start antibiotics now'). Filter outputs for non-recommendation framing ('Pattern is consistent with early sepsis' is acceptable; 'this is sepsis' is not). Log every prompt and response to the audit trail tied to the alert ID; the prompt-response pair is part of the evidence-of-decision under the FDA CDS exemption (the clinician must be able to see the reasoning that underlies the alert). See Chapter 2's generative AI recipes for the established BAA discipline." Add a forward reference to the Chapter 2 recipes that established this pattern.[K
