[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    123[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Why-These-Services "Amazon Comprehend Medical for nursing note feature extraction" paragraph; "The Technology" Features-That-Actually-Matter Nursing-Assessments subsection (Rothman-Index reference and the trade-off framing).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    124[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies that nursing-note features can be extracted via Comprehend Medical and that the Rothman Index famously builds primarily on nursing-recorded data. The Comprehend Medical paragraph names the use case ("Comprehend Medical extracts structured entities (mental status descriptions, pain assessments, concerns expressed). The extracted entities feed the feature engine."). But the PHI-handling discipline for the nursing-note ingest path is not specified: where the raw nursing-note text lives (presumably S3 with KMS), how it reaches Comprehend Medical (synchronous DetectEntitiesV2 calls from the feature-engine Lambda, or asynchronous batch jobs), what data Comprehend Medical retains (per the BAA, none beyond the request lifetime), what the audit trail for the entity-extraction call looks like, and whether the extracted entities are stored alongside or instead of the raw note (storing both creates two PHI surfaces for the same content).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    125[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    126[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe minimum-necessary discipline matters here too: the feature engine probably only needs the structured entities (mental-status flag, pain score, nursing-concern flag), not the full extracted-entity payload. A naive implementation that stores the full Comprehend Medical output as a feature carries the original note's content forward in structured form, expanding the PHI surface.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    127[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the Comprehend Medical paragraph: "Comprehend Medical's DetectEntitiesV2 is HIPAA-eligible under the BAA; PHI is processed transiently and not retained by Comprehend Medical beyond the request lifetime. The feature-engine Lambda calls DetectEntitiesV2 synchronously with the relevant nursing-note excerpt (not the full chart) and persists only the derived feature flags (mental-status documented as altered, pain score, nursing-concern flag); the full Comprehend Medical entity payload is not stored alongside the feature flags. CloudTrail data events on the DetectEntitiesV2 call capture the audit trail. The raw nursing notes themselves remain in the EHR (the source of truth) and are not duplicated into the feature pipeline beyond the synchronous extraction call."[K
