[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    186[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mEvent-normalizer Lambda fails on a malformed message.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The EHR emits an unexpected HL7 segment (rare but happens with new EHR-vendor-specific extensions), the LOINC mapping fails because the lookup table is stale, the unit-conversion encounters an unhandled unit string, the patient master-index resolution times out. Lambda's default async retry behavior is two retries over six hours and then drop. The result is silently lost: no canonical event reaches the patient state store, no scoring fires for that patient, the rolling history is missing the data point. For a deterioration system whose value proposition depends on continuous patient state coverage, silently-failing ingestion is the worst possible failure mode.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    187[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    188[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mScoring-orchestrator Lambda fails during feature computation or scoring[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m (DynamoDB throttle on patient-state, Timestream timeout on trajectory query, SageMaker endpoint cold-start latency, Bedrock throttling on explanation generation). Same retry-then-drop pattern. The patient is not scored on the affected event. For an event-driven score path that fires on high-importance state changes (a new lactate, a new respiratory rate), a missed scoring is a missed alert opportunity that may never be caught up by the periodic-tick path within the deterioration window.[K
