[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    288[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mWithout explicit architectural primitives, shadow mode in production deployments often degenerates to "the model is in production but the alerts aren't being acted on yet," which is operationally indistinguishable from a misconfigured production deployment and produces the failure modes shadow mode is meant to prevent.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    289[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a paragraph to the General Architecture Pattern's "Retraining and threshold review" subsection naming the shadow-deployment primitive: "Before any new model variant is promoted to production, deploy it as a shadow-mode endpoint alongside the production endpoint. The scoring orchestrator invokes both endpoints for every scoring request; the production endpoint's score drives alerting; the shadow endpoint's score is logged to a shadow-alerts OpenSearch index but does not route to pager / dashboard / EHR banner. The model team reviews shadow alerts weekly: feature-pipeline bugs (input distributions that don't match training), calibration drift (shadow score distributions that differ from training), operational integration problems (shadow alerts that would have produced unmanageable alert volume). The promotion criteria is documented and pre-approved by the clinical governance committee: shadow-mode performance, shadow-mode alert volume, shadow-mode subgroup performance. Promotion is a SageMaker Model Registry approval action that updates the production endpoint; rollback is an immediate revert to the previous production endpoint." Add a "Shadow deployment" line to Step 5: "If a shadow-mode endpoint is configured, invoke both endpoints, log both scores, but route only on the production endpoint's score."[K
