[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    327[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly specifies CloudTrail (with data events on every PHI-bearing store and the audit indexes) for control-plane and data-plane API audit. It does not explicitly require VPC Flow Logs, which capture network-level access patterns (source/destination IPs, ports, protocols, accept/reject) and are part of the standard HIPAA audit posture and the FDA-CDS-exemption documentation posture (the audit trail has to demonstrate that the system operated as designed).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    328[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    329[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mFor a clinical decision support system that may end up in front of a clinical-safety-review committee, network-level audit is the complement to API-level audit. CloudTrail records "who called the API" but doesn't record "which IP addresses talked to which IP addresses inside the VPC." Investigators reconstructing access patterns to alert state or to the patient state store (was there an exfiltration attempt? was a clinician's account compromised?) need both layers. Same recurring chapter-wide finding as Recipes 3.2 N2, 3.3 N2, 3.4 N2, 3.5 N2, 3.6 N2.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    330[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add to the VPC row or to the CloudTrail row: "VPC Flow Logs enabled on the VPC carrying Lambda, SageMaker, OpenSearch, Timestream, AppSync, and HealthLake traffic; logs delivered to a dedicated S3 bucket with KMS encryption and retention aligned to the deepest applicable retention requirement (clinical-safety-review documentation may extend retention requirements; FDA-CDS-exemption documentation similarly; coordinate with regulatory affairs and clinical governance for the appropriate retention schedule)."[K
