[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    344[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m####[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhat's Done Well[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    345[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    346[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe opening 3:14 a.m. medical-surgical-floor sepsis vignette is publication-ready voice. The 32-bed floor, the night shift charge nurse with eight patients on her side and the other charge nurse with six and the shared CNA, the 67-year-old woman two days post-op from a colon resection, the 11 p.m. vitals charted as "mostly normal" by single-threshold rules (temp 37.8, HR 92, BP 118/72, RR 18, SpO2 96%, mentation appropriate, pain 3/10), the next-vitals-due-at-3 a.m. operational reality, the daughter pressing the call button at 1:40 a.m., the patient oriented to person but not place, the recollect vitals (temp 38.6, HR 118, BP 92/54, RR 24, SpO2 91%), the hospitalist paged, the sepsis protocol activated, the lactate of 4.2, the broad-spectrum antibiotics at 2:38 a.m., the ICU transfer at 4:15 a.m. for vasopressors, the patient surviving with nine extra days of stay and three weeks of inpatient rehab, the data trail of HR climbing from 78 to 92 over eight hours and RR from 14 to 18 and temperature from 37.1 to 37.8 and white count of 14.2 and creatinine 0.3 above baseline and the 9 p.m. nursing note ("patient appears slightly more somnolent than earlier shift, easily arousable") is the densest sepsis-deterioration framing in any cookbook recipe to date. The closing line ("That's patient deterioration early warning. Not 'is this patient critically ill right now?' The hospital's existing critical value rules and rapid response triggers handle the obvious. The harder question is: which patients on the floor right now are showing the early signs of deterioration, hours before they hit any single alarm threshold, so the team can intervene before the call button gets pressed at 1:40 a.m.") lands the operational reality and the system reframe in two sentences without rhetorical excess.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    347[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "the reason the problem is hard, and the reason it lands at the complex end of this chapter" framing followed by seven substantive paragraphs (time is asymmetric; baselines are deeply personal; context is everything; multiple deterioration phenotypes look different; workflow integration is the actual product; regulatory and legal exposure is real; bias and equity are first-order concerns) is the right pedagogical scoping. Each paragraph ties to a specific deterioration-domain concern that distinguishes the problem from other anomaly-detection problems. The "asymmetric in both directions, with a non-linear interaction term" framing on alert-fatigue is the kind of detail-level teaching the cookbook is built on.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    348[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The track-and-trigger lineage subsection is clinically accurate. MEWS, NEWS, NEWS2, qSOFA, PEWS, SIRS each get a substantive paragraph with the right operational distinctions. The "score of 4 from two parameters slightly off is treated the same as a 4 from one parameter way off" framing is the kind of math-meets-clinical-reasoning teaching that distinguishes the cookbook from documentation.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    349[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "what ML adds (and where it adds less than vendors suggest)" subsection is the right pedagogical reframe. The closing posture ("The vendor literature talks a lot about model performance and not enough about the workflow problem; the published peer-reviewed literature is more honest about it") sets up the rest of the recipe well.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    350[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "two big vendor models, and why you should know their reputations" subsection is unusually candid and is the cookbook's first published treatment of vendor-versus-build for clinical ML. Naming Epic Deterioration Index and eCART by name, naming the 2021 Wong et al. external validation study and its finding, and the explicit "the right answer for many hospitals is to deploy a commercial model with strong local validation rather than build from scratch" framing is the design lesson most first-time builders miss.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    351[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The statistical-and-ML-methods subsection is the broadest method survey in any chapter-3 recipe (eight method families with one-to-two-paragraph treatments each). The closing "reasonable progression" posture is operationally accurate and is the kind of operations-engineer voice the cookbook is built on.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    352[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The outcome-definition subsection is unusually substantive and is the recipe's most operationally-actionable contribution. ICU transfer, cardiac arrest and code blue, composite endpoints, mortality, phenotype-specific outcomes, time-windowed prediction each get a substantive paragraph with the right operational caveats. The closing "use a composite endpoint on a 6-24 hour prediction window with phenotype-specific stratification as a secondary analysis" is the practical guidance most published treatments dance around.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    353[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The features-that-actually-matter subsection has eleven feature classes with substantive teaching content. The closing "a useful model has 50-200 features. More is not better" is the right scoping.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    354[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The sampling-time-windows-and-right-censoring subsection correctly names time-grid snapping with the artifact caveat, prediction-window construction with the patient-level train/test split discipline, right-censoring with the survival-modeling alternative, event leakage with the 30-60 minute lookahead boundary, and treatment leakage with the antibiotics-versus-deterioration confounding. Treatment leakage in particular is the single most consequential modeling concern the recipe identifies, and the framing is correct.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    355[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The calibration-matters-as-much-as-discrimination subsection is the recipe's biggest pedagogical contribution. The framing ("A score of 0.6 has to mean '60% chance of deterioration in the prediction window' if the threshold is going to be set sensibly") is the lesson most ML-on-clinical-data treatments skip.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    356[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The subgroup-performance-is-operations-work-not-a-one-time-audit subsection is correct and substantive. The named mitigations (subgroup-stratified threshold tuning, subgroup-specific recalibration, fairness-aware training, ongoing audit cycles) are concrete and operationally actionable.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    357[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The alert-fatigue-is-a-design-constraint subsection is publication-ready voice and uses concrete numbers (300 inpatients, 7,200 daily evaluations, 360 false positives per day at 95% specificity, RRT page every four minutes) to make the design implications obvious. The six design implications are concrete and operationally actionable.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    358[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take is publication-ready and should be preserved verbatim. The eleven lessons land the right teaching priorities. The closing "I want to say this clearly because it's easy to get lost in the operational difficulty: when these systems work, they work" framing is the kind of moral-clarity framing that distinguishes the cookbook from documentation. The references to Kaiser Permanente AAM and University of Chicago eCART published outcomes data are clinically accurate and operationally meaningful.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    359[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Variations and Extensions section covers the right adjacent patterns at substantive depth. Eleven extensions each with one-to-two paragraphs covering sepsis-specific, respiratory-failure-specific, post-operative, pediatric, maternal-fetal, ICU de-escalation, ED admission decisions, RPM, LLM-enhanced explanation, multi-modal, federated learning, closed-loop. The closed-loop framing is appropriately cautious about the FDA SaMD escalation.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    360[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m Style hygiene is exceptionally clean: zero em dashes (verified directly with U+2014 character check), zero en dashes (U+2013 verified), no marketing language, no documentation-voice. The 70/30 vendor balance is preserved cleanly. HTML-comment TODO discipline is correct (eight TODOs, all forward-placeholder, no bracket-style visible TODOs).[K
