[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    418[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPattern: A1 (outcome-event idempotency) is the now-recurring trigger-idempotency finding, surfacing for the twelfth consecutive recipe (2.4-2.10 and 3.1-3.7).[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Same fix template (deterministic event-key derivation, conditional-write enforcement at the orchestration layer), different specific event source (clinical outcome events from the EHR plus clinician acknowledgment events from the UI here). For Recipe 3.7 the consequence is calibrated to the supervised-retraining pathway: doubled label rows on positive cases (which are rare and precious) distort the supervised classifier's class balance and produce a model that over-fires on patterns that happened to have been redelivered during the training window. With this finding now flagged across twelve consecutive recipes, the per-recipe-edit posture is producing diminishing returns. The cookbook editor should treat the trigger-idempotency appendix as the highest-leverage cookbook-wide editorial investment.[K
